The mayor of the city of Johannesburg, Geoff Makhubo, has died. MMC for finance in the city Jolidee Matongo confirmed  the mayor has passed away but could not  provide more details. On July 3, the city said Makhubo, 53, had been hospitalised with Covid-19 complications. He was diagnosed with the coronavirus late last month and had gone into self-quarantine. This is a developing story TimesLIVE